In a teleconference with Jewish leaders, President Biden apologized for not being able to host a celebration at the White House for the High Holidays due to COVID-19. He emphasized the importance of renewal and restoring America's soul, stating that America is an idea based on the belief that all men and women are created equal. He spoke about the need to bridge gaps, rebuild communities through empathy and kindness, and address societal challenges such as anti-Semitism. President Biden also expressed his commitment to the security of Israel and the integration of newcomers. He acknowledged the challenges ahead but drew hope from Jewish history and tradition. The President ended by quoting an Irish poet and expressing his belief in the possibility of making things better.